The family of Tanzanian artiste turned politician Prof Jay has refuted claims he is dead. The rapper’s younger brother Black Rhyno told Global Publishers his fans should ignore the rumours. "It is a lie. He is not dead. Let us stop saying things that are not true." A Tanzanian politician by the name John Heche also shut down the rumours. "News about Prof Jay are not true," he tweeted. Jay has been in hospital for weeks, including in the ICU. He is said to be suffering from high blood pressure and is also alleged to be battling Covid -19. The ex-MP is currently undergoing dialysis as his kidneys have been affected. A source told Word Is his health is deteriorating fast but he is fighting for his life.